version_description: This version sounds good when played with the album version.
None of the chords here are simplified. Playing Bm G Em G sounds fine as a simplification for the pre-chorus and chorus.
This is the studio version of this song. If you take time to play along to the vid on youtube you can see the timing and chords are spot on.

Simple, but fairly accurate version of the song. Wasn't too sure how long to make the intro (don't tend to play it myself) but basically just repeat the Am/Dm as much as is necessary. The F in the chorus is optionally (personally i don't play it) so yeh up to you. Written for guitar but, having tried it, it works really well on ukulele too.
Standard tuning, no capo, chords used: Cm, Eb, Fm.
Whole song tabbed out except solo.
Pretty simple, just repeat these 3 chords the whole time and add some flair if you're feeling it.
I used Am, C, G, D for a mor simple version. It's not exactly like the original song.
